From: DOSKUTSU NXEngine Port <services.claude@accounts.ecliptik.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 17:46:42 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] [DOSKUTSU] SDL3 renderer-properties API migration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Why DOS needs this: the SDL2 SDL_RendererInfo struct + SDL_GetRendererInfo()
function are removed in SDL3, replaced by an SDL_PropertiesID-based query.
This is a "genuinely different API surface" change rather than a rename, so
the brief (patches/nxengine-evo/README.md) splits it from 0010.

Site: src/graphics/Renderer.cpp Renderer::initVideo() (~lines 127-134).

Old SDL2 pattern:
    SDL_RendererInfo info;
    if (SDL_GetRendererInfo(_renderer, &info)) { LOG_ERROR(...); return false; }
    LOG_INFO("... using: {} renderer", info.name);

New SDL3 pattern:
    SDL_PropertiesID props = SDL_GetRendererProperties(_renderer);
    const char *name = SDL_GetStringProperty(props,
                                             SDL_PROP_RENDERER_NAME_STRING,
                                             NULL);
    LOG_INFO("... using: {} renderer", name ? name : "<unknown>");

Notes:

- SDL_GetRendererProperties returns 0 only on a NULL renderer; we already
  guarded for that earlier in initVideo, so we don't error-check it here.
- SDL_GetStringProperty returns the default (NULL) if the property isn't
  set; we fall back to "<unknown>" in the log line rather than failing init.
- The log line is the only consumer of info.name in NXEngine — no other
  RendererInfo fields (flags, max_texture_width, etc.) are read.

After this patch, the 0010-0012 cluster makes NXEngine-evo compile against
SDL3 headers for the renderer subsystem. Audio (Mix_*, SDL_AudioCVT) and
SDL3_image (IMG_*) calls remain to be migrated by 0013-0017 / 0018.
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp | 15 +++++++--------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 8 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index b80f02b..598f8db 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -153,14 +153,13 @@ bool Renderer::initVideo()
     return false;
   }
 
-  SDL_RendererInfo info;
-  if (SDL_GetRendererInfo(_renderer, &info))
-  {
-    LOG_ERROR("Renderer::initVideo: SDL_GetRendererInfo failed: {}", SDL_GetError());
-    return false;
-  }
-
-  LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: using: {} renderer", info.name);
+  // SDL3: SDL_RendererInfo struct + SDL_GetRendererInfo() are gone. The replacement
+  // is the SDL_PropertiesID-based query: SDL_GetRendererProperties() returns the
+  // renderer's property bag, then SDL_GetStringProperty() pulls named values out.
+  // SDL_PROP_RENDERER_NAME_STRING is the renderer-driver name (e.g. "software").
+  SDL_PropertiesID _renderer_props = SDL_GetRendererProperties(_renderer);
+  const char *_renderer_name = SDL_GetStringProperty(_renderer_props, SDL_PROP_RENDERER_NAME_STRING, NULL);
+  LOG_INFO("Renderer::initVideo: using: {} renderer", _renderer_name ? _renderer_name : "<unknown>");
 
   std::string spotpath = ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPath("spot.png");
 
